1. Edit cbgraph-logo.odg with LibreOfficeDraw

2. Export to 
      application-x-cbgraphfile.svg
      cbgraph-logo-ORIGSIZE.png

3. Scale cbgraph-logo-ORIGSIZE.png to size 48
    as cbgraph-logo-48x48.gif

* Open cbgraph-logo-ORIGSIZE.png with GIMP and export to
     cbgraph-logo-ORIGSIZE.ico (MS Icon file)

4. cp cbgraph-logo-48x48.gif ../java/resources/graph_resources/CBGraphS.gif 

5. Resize application-x-cbgraphfile.svg by inkscape to fill most of the frame

6. cp application-x-cbgraphfile.svg ~/CBPOOL/conceptbase


7. mkcb;instcb


8. cd ~/CBPOOL/conceptbase
  sudo cp application-x-cbgraphfile.svg  /usr/share/icons/gnome/scalable/mimetypes
  sudo gtk-update-icon-cache /usr/share/icons/gnome/ -f
